#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:1
msgid "The Rust Bookshelf"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: various](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-various-brightgreen.svg), each book is different."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:5
msgid ""
"As Rust's documentation has grown, we've gained far more than just \"The "
"book\" and the reference. We now have a collection of various long-form "
"docs, nicknamed \"the Rust Bookshelf.\" Different resources are added at "
"various times, and we're adding new ones as more get written."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:10
msgid "The Cargo book"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:12
#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:23
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.21](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.21-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:14
msgid ""
"Historically, Cargo’s docs were hosted on <http://doc.crates.io>, which "
"doesn’t follow the release train model, even though Cargo itself does. This "
"led to situations where a feature would land in Cargo nightly, the docs "
"would be updated, and then for up to twelve weeks, users would think that it "
"should work, but it wouldn’t yet. <https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo> is the "
"new home of Cargo’s docs, and <http://doc.crates.io> now redirects there."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:21
msgid "The `rustdoc` book"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:25
msgid ""
"Rustdoc, our documentation tool, now has a guide at <https://doc.rust-lang."
"org/rustdoc>."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:27
msgid "Rust By Example"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:29
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.25](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.25-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/documentation/the-rust-bookshelf.md:31
msgid ""
"Rust by Example used to live at <https://rustbyexample.com>, but now is part "
"of the Bookshelf! It can be found at <https://doc.rust-lang.org/rust-by-"
"example/>. RBE lets you learn Rust through short code examples and "
"exercises, as opposed to the lengthy prose of The Book."
msgstr ""
